About Me

Get to know me

My name is Logan Burns. I am currently a Freshman at the University of Florida, majoring in Electrical Engineering. I enjoy engaging in critical thought and deliberative discussion to solve

problems, regardless of the area of focus.

 

My interest in Electrical Engineering stems largely from constant proximity to computer hardware, my curiosity relating to the functionality of electrical devices, and a healthy learning environment that has motivated me to explore various STEM fields.

​

I am continuing this search throughout my undergraduate career through on-campus engagements, namely organizational involvement and research, where I intend to discover what areas of Electrical Engineering I am truly passionate for.

Research Interests

  • System on a Chip (SoC) design

  • Failure analysis of integrated circuits

  • VLSI circuits

  • Power electronics & analysis

  • Analog and mixed-signal circuits​
